Package info.addisoncrump.oklahoma.bot.minecraft.event

Event package for all Minecraft process IO events. A majority of these events are fired by MinecraftConsoleOutputParserService after a MinecraftConsoleOutputEvent instance is cleaned by MinecraftConsoleOutputCleanerService, then parsed by MinecraftConsoleOutputParserService into various events.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MinecraftCleanedConsoleOutputEvent
    Event which is fired after console cleaning.
    MinecraftConsoleOutputEvent
    Event which is fired when the Minecraft process outputs a line of logging.
    MinecraftServerShutdownEvent
    Event which is fired upon server shutdown.
    MinecraftServerStartupEvent
    Event which is fired as soon as the Minecraft process starts up.
    PlayerChatEvent
    Event which is fired when a player chat is logged by the Minecraft process (as parsed by MinecraftConsoleOutputParserService).
    PlayerConnectEvent
    Event which is fired when a player connects to the server and successfully logs in as logged by the Minecraft process and parsed by the MinecraftConsoleOutputParserService instance.
    PlayerDisconnectEvent
    Event which is fired when a player disconnects from the server as logged by the Minecraft process and parsed by the MinecraftConsoleOutputParserService instance.
